    NOW SELLING THE BLUFFS AT BELLS FERRY, A NEW GATED COMMUNITY! TRATON HOMES AWARD WINNING BROOKS H - Detached PLAN. ONE OF OUR MOST POPULAR FLOORPLANS IN WOODED ENCLAVE!! READY NOW!! This Custom two-story townhome offers a popular open concept kitchen, family room and dining area that opens to rear PATIO & private backyard which makes this home perfect for entertaining. Upstairs offers a versatile loft area and Primary Suite with impressive bath and large walk-in closet. 2 additional bedrooms, a full bath, plus the laundry room are also located on the upper level. Bluffs at Bells Ferry is nestled with the city of Marietta and is ideally positioned near Cobb Parkway & I-75 with easy access to endless shopping and dining options along Barrett Parkway and the historic Marietta Square. It is also sited near Kennesaw Mountain Park and minutes to The Battery. PHOTOS ARE REPRESENTATIVE. 3D Tour is representative. With preferred lender, Buyers may receive up to $15,000 in Closing Costs to use towards a 2/1 RATE BUYDOWN from the builder. See agent for more details. All applicants must prequalify with our lender regardless of who they chose for their loan. All incentives are tied to preferred lender only.

    Community & Neighborhood

    Community Info

    Nestled within the vibrant tapestry of the City of Marietta is Traton's newest townhome community, Bluffs at Bells Ferry. This community offers stylish two-story townhomes including the award-winning Brooks floorplan. Bluffs at Bells Ferry is ideally positioned near major thoroughfares including Cobb Parkway and I-75 with easy access to endless shopping and dining options along Barrett Parkway and the historic Marietta Square. It is also sited near Kennesaw Mountain Park as well as major employers including the Wellstar Kennestone hospital campus, making it a great option for healthcare professionals. Homes will feature 3 or 4 bedrooms, 2.5 baths and 2-car garages. Stylish kitchens with large islands, open main levels, luxurious owner's suites, spacious secondary bedrooms, and lofts are some of the exceptional features of these homes. Residents will enjoy a low-maintenance lifestyle with lawns and common areas maintained by the HOA. In this close-knit community, shared walls effortlessly translate into shared stories, fostering an environment where neighbors transform into lifelong friends. Traton Homes has been in business for over 50 years and has been named Best Builder in Cobb County for the past 3 years in a row! Discover Altogether More lifestyle, location and value at Bluffs at Bells Ferry. The community is served by Marietta City Schools, one of the proud and few nationwide school systems able to provide a full K-12 International Baccalaureate program. More Info About Bluffs at Bells Ferry.

    Builder Details

    Traton Homes

    Founded in 1971 by brothers Bill and Milburn Poston and based in Marietta, Georgia, family-owned Traton Homes is one of metro Atlanta’s oldest home builders. We’re also one of the most innovative, combining traditional building practices with a passion for the latest systems & styles. From full-featured townhomes to 55+ active adult homes to single-family detached homes, we build outstanding quality and value into every home. That means the best value today, and the opportunity for the best resale value tomorrow. We’ve been honored with numerous awards over the years. We are an eight-time recipient of the Guildmaster Award for customer service excellence and have won more than 50 OBIE Awards presented by the Greater Atlanta HBA. Our proudest achievement is that countless homeowners have chosen us for a second, or even a third new home. We’re also known as an employer of choice, and take pride in the loyalty of our team members. “There’s something about a Traton home.” We hear it often from real estate professionals and buyers. We’re constantly working to elevate that “something,” which we refer to as “Altogether More!” With over50 years in business, we know our buyers’ wants and needs and where they want to live. Walkable communities, easy thoroughfare access, exceptional shopping and dining, and the conveniences that make life relaxing and fun. We also make it enjoyable to personalize your new home. At our Design Center you’ll find a wide variety of options from which to choose. Our design consultants help buyers review these options and select features that turn a house into a one-of-a-kind home. At Traton Homes, we are happy to attract the newest generation of homeowners, even as we continue to delight their parents and grandparents who choose Traton time and time again.
